<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="270" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,310,587]" pageId="25" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,418,443]" pageId="25" pageNumber="270">Comments:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[347,512,419,443]" pageId="25" pageNumber="270" refId="ref14971" refString="Attems, C. (1899) System der Polydesmiden. II. Theil. Denkschriften der Akademie der Wissenschaften Wien, Mathematisch- Naturwissenschaftliche Klassen, 68, 251 - 436." type="journal article">Attems (1899)</bibRefCitation>
description was based on specimens from northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1165,1236,418,443]" name="Brazil" pageId="25" pageNumber="270">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, near the borders with 
<collectingCountry box="[210,261,455,478]" name="Peru" pageId="25" pageNumber="270">Peru</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[320,433,454,479]" name="Colombia" pageId="25" pageNumber="270">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, that probably correspond to a different species (
<bibRefCitation box="[996,1149,454,479]" pageId="25" pageNumber="270" refId="ref17622" refString="Pocock, R. I. (1909) Chilopoda and Diplopoda. In: Godman, F. D. &amp; Salvin, O. (Eds.), Biologia centrali-americana, contributions to the knowledge of the fauna and flora of Mexico and Central America. Porter &amp; Co., London, pp. 89 - 200." type="book chapter">Pocock 1909</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[1162,1332,454,479]" pageId="25" pageNumber="270" refId="ref16185" refString="Hoffman, R. L. (1960) A fourth contribution to the knowledge of Neotropical platyrhacid millipeds (Diplopoda: Polydesmida). Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 111, 17 - 31. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.111 - 3423.17" type="journal article">Hoffman 1960</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation pageId="25" pageNumber="270" refId="ref17622" refString="Pocock, R. I. (1909) Chilopoda and Diplopoda. In: Godman, F. D. &amp; Salvin, O. (Eds.), Biologia centrali-americana, contributions to the knowledge of the fauna and flora of Mexico and Central America. Porter &amp; Co., London, pp. 89 - 200." type="book chapter">Pocock (1909)</bibRefCitation>
suggested affinities with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Attems, 1899)" authorityName="Attems" authorityYear="1899" baseAuthorityName="Attems" baseAuthorityYear="1899" box="[516,974,490,515]" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Nyssodesmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="25" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limonensis">
<emphasis box="[516,793,490,515]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="270">Nyssodesmus limonensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[808,966,491,515]" pageId="25" pageNumber="270" refId="ref14971" refString="Attems, C. (1899) System der Polydesmiden. II. Theil. Denkschriften der Akademie der Wissenschaften Wien, Mathematisch- Naturwissenschaftliche Klassen, 68, 251 - 436." type="journal article">Attems, 1899</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[986,1169,490,515]" pageId="25" pageNumber="270" refId="ref16346" refString="Hoffman, R. L. (1999) Checklist of the millipedes of North and Middle America. Virginia Museum of Natural History Special Publication, 8, 1 - 584." type="journal article">Hoffman (1999)</bibRefCitation>
suggested it could be a species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1896" box="[269,406,526,551]" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Barydesmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="25" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[269,406,526,551]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="270">Barydesmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Currently there are no verified records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1895" box="[886,1038,526,551]" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="25" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Platyrhacidae</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[1074,1159,526,551]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="25" pageNumber="270">
<collectingCountry box="[1074,1159,526,551]" name="Mexico" pageId="25" pageNumber="270">Mexico</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[1173,1342,526,551]" pageId="25" pageNumber="270" refId="ref16346" refString="Hoffman, R. L. (1999) Checklist of the millipedes of North and Middle America. Virginia Museum of Natural History Special Publication, 8, 1 - 584." type="journal article">Hoffman 1999</bibRefCitation>
; Bueno- Villegas 
<emphasis box="[249,298,562,587]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="270">et al</emphasis>
. 2004).
</paragraph>
